					<description><![CDATA[<p>The holiday season is the perfect time to connect with prospects and customers in a fun and memorable way. Here are 18 festive holiday marketing ideas to get your wheels turning.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2017/10/17/holiday-marketing-ideas">18 Fun &#038; Festive Holiday Marketing Ideas to Try This Year</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>With pumpkin spice lattes back in season, it is hard not to have the holidays on our minds. Halloween is creeping up on us, and we‚Äôre about to be in full-out holiday season. What could be more exciting?</p>
<p>In fact, the holiday season is a perfect time to connect with your customers in a cheery way. Whether it be to show your loyal clients you care, to warm up current leads, or even to entice new ones with some powerful branding campaigns, there‚Äôs a tremendous chance to use the seasons to your marketing benefit.</p>
<p>Here are our top captivating holiday marketing ideas to get the wheels turning.</p>
<h3>Contents</h3>
<ol>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-google-ads-search">Create seasonal Google Ads search campaigns</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-shopping-ads">Gift yourself with Google Shopping Ads</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-instagram-ads">Step up your Instagram ad game</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-social-media-giveaway">Run a holiday giveaway on social media</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-email">Get seasonal in email</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-remarketing">Rev up your remarketing strategy</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-audience-segmentation">Reimagine your audience segmentation strategy</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-webinar">Conduct a holiday-themed webinar</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-heartstrings">Make your holiday marketing pull at the heartstrings</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-video">Get creative with holiday video marketing</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-party">Throw a holiday party</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-amazon">Advertise on Amazon</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-display-ads">Create festive and entertaining display ads</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-loyalty-gifts">Build customer loyalty with personalized gifts</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-appreciation-email">Send out a (good!) customer appreciation email</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-year-in-review-email">Try a year-in-review email</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-playlist">Create a shareable holiday playlist</a></li>
<li><a href="#holiday-marketing-ideas-ai">Use AI to create unique holiday marketing copy and creative assets</a></li>
</ol>
<h2>Holiday marketing ideas any business can try</h2>
<p>Check out these <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/12/07/january-marketing-ideas">holiday marketing ideas</a> that are a guaranteed fit for any<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/05/11/target-audience" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> target audience</a>.</p>
<p><strong><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f5d3.png" alt="üóì" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> Want marketing ideas that last beyond the holiday season?</strong> Get marketing inspiration and tips for the entire year with our free <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/resources/marketing-calendar?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Guide_2025MarketingCalendar_Download&amp;itm_source=wordstream&amp;itm_medium=blog&amp;itm_campaign=incontent_links" target="_blank" rel="noopener">2025 marketing calendar</a>!</p>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-google-ads-search"></div>
<h3>1. Create seasonal Google Ads search campaigns</h3>
<p>Whether you‚Äôre in retail, B2B, finance, or insurance, <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/performance-max-holiday-strategies">Google Ads</a> is a great place to get seasonal! How can one do this? Create a campaign targeting holiday shoppers!</p>
<p>For instance, if you sell women‚Äôs apparel, you can target keywords like ‚Äúgifts for mother‚Äù or ‚Äúholiday sweaters.‚Äù Then create specific ads and landing pages offering incentives to shop with your store during the holiday season.</p>
<p>Perhaps you give free shipping if they purchase over $100 worth of clothing? Or let‚Äôs say you gift wrap for free? Maybe you offer $20 off if the gift is ordered before a certain date? Highlight these benefits and make sure your landing pages capture the spirit of the holidays.</p>
<p>Not in B2C? Not to worry! There are still ways to get creative with your Google Ads campaigns during the holidays. As holiday shopping goes underway everyone is looking for ways to cut costs, so promote some special seasonal discounts on AdWords. Take advantage of ad extensions to take up more space in the results, get a higher chance of site visits, and highlight the special things your company is doing for the season.</p>
<p>Here are a few quick Google Ads holiday marketing tips to remember:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Use seasonal ad copy.</strong> Include words and phrases like ‚Äúholiday‚Äù and ‚Äú&#8217;tis the season.‚Äù</li>
<li><strong>Don&#8217;t use cliches. </strong>Use these <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/11/01/holiday-copywriting">ideas for cliche-free holiday copywriting</a> instead.</li>
<li><strong>Ad assets are your friends.</strong> Enhancing your ads with additional ad assets will help you eat up more real estate on the SERP during this competitive time.</li>
<li><strong>Highlight special offers.</strong> Be sure to capitalize on any seasonal deals you may be running.</li>
<li><strong>Instill a sense of urgency. </strong>Use copy like ‚Äú40% off if you order before Dec 15!‚Äù or ‚ÄúTake Advantage Before It‚Äôs Too Late!‚Äù</li>
<li><strong>Make sure you‚Äôre relevant. </strong>Conduct holiday-related <a href="/keywords">keyword research</a>.</li>
<li><strong>Set up ad scheduling.</strong> That way, you can bid on the times when your shoppers are searching.</li>
</ul>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="0bcaf298-d095-4490-8998-0a3d401b3c63" data-langcode="en"></div>
<p>Keep in mind that everyone is looking for a deal during the holiday season! Pairing this with <a href="/blog/ws/2017/04/05/how-to-increase-urgency">a sense of urgency</a> in your¬†ad copy is a way is a great way to win over hectic seasonal shoppers.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/holiday-ppc-mistakes-search-ad-example-with-holiday-copy.png" alt="holiday marketing ideas - holiday google ad example" width="281" height="500" class="aligncenter wp-image-49597 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/holiday-ppc-mistakes-search-ad-example-with-holiday-copy.png 281w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/holiday-ppc-mistakes-search-ad-example-with-holiday-copy-169x300.png 169w" sizes="(max-width: 281px) 100vw, 281px" /></p>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-shopping-ads"></div>
<h3>2. Gift yourself with Google Shopping Ads</h3>
<p>If you sell physical products and you‚Äôre not already using Google Shopping, now is the time to treat yourself to your first Google Shopping campaign! These are the perfect treat for your busy online holiday shoppers because they‚Äôre extremely convenient and can lead to purchases happening almost instantaneously.</p>
<p>Of course, the challenge will be standing out next to your competition in such a visual manner, but as long as your images are enticing and your campaign is set up properly, these babies can work wonders on converting shoppers during the holiday season. Check out our guide to get started if you‚Äôre new to <a href="/blog/ws/2015/03/04/google-shopping-campaigns-tips-tricks">Google Shopping</a>.</p>
<p><img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/16.0.1/72x72/1f6a8.png" alt="üö®" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><strong> Is your Google Ads account ready for the holiday rush?</strong> Find out with our <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Free Google Ads Grader</a>!</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="9c8d611b-5180-475a-8c4b-1ebe6aca34e5" data-langcode="en">
<article>
<div></div>
</article>
</div>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-instagram-ads"></div>
<h3>3. Step up your Instagram ad game</h3>
<p>Instagram is the perfect place to make your holiday game shine! Users are already there posting family selfies and pictures of their decorations, so why not break through the clutter with a fun holiday ad? While posting organically to your account is great as well, to really stand out it‚Äôs worth throwing some money behind your very best holiday pics.</p>
<p>Whether it be your team dressed in ugly sweaters or your office dog with a monster mask on, get creative and cheery and bring in those <a href="/blog/ws/2017/05/22/best-instagram-ads">Instagram hearts</a>! Check out this example from a restaurant in my neighborhood. Not only did they get seasonal with a new drink recipe (pumpkin margarita, yum!), but they placed it near a carved pumpkin and used some seasonal emojis in their ad copy.</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="fff0d582-dfaa-45ed-ab98-9a92204c040b" data-langcode="en">
<article>
<div><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/holiday-themed-instagram-ads.jpg" alt="marketing on instagram for the holiday season" width="807" height="575" class="aligncenter" /></div>
</article>
</div>
<p style="text-align: center;"><em>Here are some more great tips for <a href="/blog/ws/2017/07/06/instagram-marketing-for-restaurants">marketing a restaurant on Instagram </a>like the example above.¬†</em></p>
<p>We predict social shopping will be a huge <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/08/29/holiday-marketing-trends">holiday marketing trend</a> this year. Get tips to capitalize on it!</p>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-social-media-giveaway"></div>
<h3>4. Run a holiday giveaway on social media</h3>
<p>Speaking of Instagram, another great way to utilize the platform is by running a <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/social-media-holidays/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">social holiday</a> giveaway. I‚Äôd recommend running a social campaign across all the major platforms your business uses (Facebook, Snapchat, Twitter, etc.) to get more and more eyes on your business.</p>
<p>And who doesn‚Äôt like free stuff, especially during the holidays (hello, re-gifting!)? Whether it be a big discount, a free add-on with an order or just something completely for free, get into the holiday spirit of giving. Typically, asking followers to comment, share, like, etc. are great tactics to get even more engagement on your <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/holiday-giveaways/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">giveaway</a>.</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="10c2714c-b45c-4da3-ac97-3b206a487df9" data-langcode="en">
<article>
<div><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/instagram-giveaways-example.jpg" alt="holiday marketing on instagram" width="1400" height="1400" /></div>
</article>
</div>
<p>Check out Dan‚Äôs guide on <a href="/blog/ws/2017/05/11/instagram-giveaways">how to use an Instagram giveaway to grow your following</a>, and for even more ideas and inspiration check out some <a href="/blog/ws/2017/03/24/best-instagram-marketing-campaigns">Instagram marketing campaigns</a> we loved!</p>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-email"></div>
<h3>5. Get seasonal in email</h3>
<p>If you‚Äôre not incorporating the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2022/12/01/holiday-email-templates">holidays into your email marketing campaigns</a>, you‚Äôre making a big mistake! Holidays instill powerful memories into your shoppers‚Äô minds, so enticing them with fun seasonal emails is a great way to connect in their inboxes.</p>
<p>For instance, this marketing email from Rent the Runway instantly caught my eye. I may not have ended up renting for Halloween specifically, but it did remind me that I could use their service for an upcoming wedding.</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="cc1c465c-40ea-462a-90b2-ade6594b83b4" data-langcode="en">
<article>
<div><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/holiday-seasonal-email-marketing-ideas.jpg" alt="holiday season email marketing ideas" width="555" height="664" /></div>
</article>
</div>
<p>Pay close attention to your <a href="/blog/ws/2014/03/31/email-subject-lines">email subject lines</a> when marketing for the holidays. Similar to ad copy in your seasonal Google Ads campaigns, it‚Äôs important to give them an incentive to shop with you, and instilling urgency is a great strategy for your subject lines.</p>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-remarketing"></div>
<h3>6. Rev up your remarketing strategy</h3>
<p>Remember that time you almost bought that dress, and then you saw it again and took that as a sign, so you went ahead and bought it? Sadly, that was not fate, that was remarketing! <a href="/google-remarketing">Remarketing</a> is when you cookie your audience to later remind them what they‚Äôre missing out on.</p>
<p>Hopefully, you‚Äôre already remarketing, but if you aren‚Äôt you need to be! Remarketing gives you a chance to remind potential customers that they abandoned their shopping cart or landing page. The holiday season is what I like to call a <strong>mandatory remarketing season</strong> because people are busy and making decisions fast. Therefore, if they dropped off your website or <a href="/blog/ws/2016/03/17/shopping-cart-abandonment">left their cart half full</a>, they might just need a quick reminder.</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="fec949f4-ef66-47c2-a802-71a8e3ee4687" data-langcode="en">
<article>
<div></div>
</article>
</div>
<p>This is where remarketing comes into play. When configuring your remarking lists for the holidays, ensure your membership duration is shorter than normal. For instance, if you typically allow users to be added to your remarking list for 30 days, reduce that to 15 days. That will increase the chances of the individual seeing your ads more frequently closer to the holiday.</p>
<p>And make sure you‚Äôre remarketing on all the channels you‚Äôre running <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/10/08/holiday-advertising-best-practices-2020">holiday advertising </a>on (Facebook, Google, Instagram, Bing, etc.)</p>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-audience-segmentation"></div>
<h3>7. Reimagine your audience segmentation strategy</h3>
<p>As a digital marketer, you and I both know that you‚Äôre sitting on piles of user data that you can use to your benefit for future campaigns. The question is, are you actually using this data?</p>
<p>If not, there is no better time to get crafty with your <a href="/blog/ws/2017/08/28/behavioral-segmentation">segmentation</a> messaging than the holiday season! Personalizing your messaging is a proven strategy to connect with consumers on a deeper level. If you have a large segment of mothers who express interest in your products or services, create content that shows how your business empathizes with how stressful the holidays can be with a full house of kids. Target a segment of leads with similar hobbies with ad copy relevant to those interests.</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="3aaaf212-42bd-4ea9-a422-b9d2c6aa1b42" data-langcode="en">
<article>
<div><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/behavioral-targeting-and-segmentation-strategies-facebook.jpg" alt="marketing segmentation on facebook" width="800" height="558" /></div>
</article>
</div>
<p>Utilizing the data you‚Äôve collected through platforms like Facebook, GA4, and Google Ads is a great place to start. Also, take advantage of lookalike audiences on these platforms to go after a new segment of leads similar to a high-converting audience.</p>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-webinar"></div>
<h3>8. Conduct a holiday-themed webinar</h3>
<p>Does your company hold a weekly, monthly, or even quarterly webinar for customers or prospects? Webinars are a great way to teach your audience in a more personalized manner, which can in-turn lead to a natural sale or upsell.</p>
<p>However, webinars are common. I probably get about 20-60 webinar invites in my inbox every month from various companies I‚Äôve come across over the years, but the problem is those webinar invites often go unnoticed. This is where holidays can really help add a fun element to an otherwise rudimentary webinar invite.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/holiday-marketing-webinars-e1732544060831.jpg" alt="holiday marketing ideas - webinar example" width="600" height="463" class="aligncenter wp-image-18592 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/holiday-marketing-webinars-e1732544060831.jpg 600w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/holiday-marketing-webinars-e1732544060831-480x270.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw" /></p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="cd302654-522e-4d44-8fc3-9ecd27916f2c" data-langcode="en">
<article>
<div></div>
</article>
</div>
<p>To <a href="/blog/ws/2016/05/03/marketing-webinars">make your webinar even more enticing</a>, tempt your audience with a free gift. For example, at the end of the webinar offer attendees a holiday discount code or free shipping on their next order.</p>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-heartstrings"></div>
<h3>9. Make your holiday marketing pull at the heartstrings</h3>
<p>When I picture the holidays I see Christmas lights, cookies, Santa Claus, and reindeer, but what I feel is that warm fuzzy feeling of enjoying time with family. While holidays may not be loved by all, most people have an emotional tie to them. And we all know that <a href="/blog/ws/2017/06/01/high-converting-landing-page-images">emotions drive action</a>, so now is the time to get emotional with your marketing.</p>
<p>Emotional doesn‚Äôt mean you need to make every one of your audience members cry ‚Äì even using humor in your messaging can go a long way during the holiday season. If you need some inspiration, check out these resources:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/01/13/best-words-and-phrases-for-marketing/">The best words and phrases for marketing with emotion</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/05/03/emotional-marketing-copy/">Emotional trigger words for compelling content</a></li>
</ul>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-video"></div>
<h3>10. Get creative with holiday video marketing</h3>
<p>There is no better way to communicate a holiday message than with video. Whether it‚Äôs a festive webinar invite video that you send via email, a video added to your customer page to wish all of your customers holiday cheer, or a wacky video that you post on social media of your CEO dressed as a reindeer, get creative, and have fun with video to spread the cheer throughout your marketing campaigns.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/holiday-marketing-video-ideas-e1732544267653.jpg" alt="holiday marketing ideas - video example" width="672" height="386" class="aligncenter wp-image-18594 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/holiday-marketing-video-ideas-e1732544267653.jpg 672w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/holiday-marketing-video-ideas-e1732544267653-480x270.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 672px, 100vw" /></p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="f40757b4-7a41-4b26-ad19-75d2032bdfa7" data-langcode="en">
<article>
<div></div>
</article>
</div>
<p class="text-align-center" style="text-align: center;"><em>A fun <a href="https://www.facebook.com/wistia/videos/10154172501963031/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">holiday-themed video</a> example.</em></p>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-party"></div>
<h3>11. Throw a holiday party</h3>
<p>Throw a holiday party? Ho-ho-hold up! That sounds expensive‚Ä¶ Well, it can be, but you can be strategic as to who you invite. For instance, you may decide to focus your invitations on a select group of your hottest local leads, and simply have them come to the office for some holiday drinks, appetizers, and games. There‚Äôs no better way to build strong relationship with prospects and customers then giving them actual face time, so why not use the holidays as an excuse to do just that. Create a festive e-invite, and get the eggnog cooking!</p>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-amazon"></div>
<h3>12. Advertise on Amazon</h3>
<p>If you‚Äôre in the retail business, you need to be putting some money into your Amazon ads.</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="6d3ebb13-a396-4d8c-bcf8-3b6effb1b596" data-langcode="en">
<article>
<div><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/amazon-ads-holiday-marketing-ideas.jpg" alt="amazon marketing campaigns" width="270" height="469" /></div>
</article>
</div>
<p>James Thomson, <a href="https://www.bigcommerce.com/blog/holiday-marketing-campaigns/#cmtoc_anchor_id_6" target="_blank" rel="noopener">President of Prosper Show</a>, has some advice for Amazon advertisers to abide by during the holidays. ‚ÄúIf you sell on Amazon, be sure to get your FBA inventory to Amazon by November 10, at the latest,‚Äù says Thomson. ‚ÄúIf you expect to sell through most inventory, calculate the cost of a stock-out vs. holding more inventory‚Ä¶. It‚Äôs usually better to have more inventory in FBA. And don‚Äôt forget to plan for inventory you expect to sell in January‚Ä¶so many companies run out of inventory in early January when suppliers are slow to replenish.‚Äù</p>
<p>Unfamiliar or unsure if you want to advertise on Amazon? Check out this <a href="/blog/ws/2017/09/11/amazon-advertising">guide to learn all the details about advertising on Amazon</a>.</p>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-display-ads"></div>
<h3>13. Create festive and entertaining display ads</h3>
<p>Do you have an in-house designer? Perfect! If not, you might want to start thinking about your needs from outside resources soon to plan for your holiday display campaigns.</p>
<p>Festive <a href="/blog/ws/2017/09/26/how-to-create-facebook-ads">images on Facebook</a> and the Google Display Network can really help create a cheerful connection between your brand and your leads. The example ad below from Hotel Tonight‚Äôs holiday campaign last year really hit the nail on the head. The image pops out and immediately grabs you in, and makes you laugh because who doesn‚Äôt have the one (or more than one) crazy relative? This ad is relatable, entertaining, and festive all at once.</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.simple_image" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="caae3ed8-1330-4f32-b00f-2a9c18d7f62f" data-langcode="en">
<article>
<div><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/funny-holiday-display-ads.jpg" alt="holiday ad campaigns" width="600" height="1200" /></div>
</article>
</div>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-loyalty-gifts"></div>
<h3>14. Build customer loyalty with personalized gifts</h3>
<p>Last, but definitely not least, don‚Äôt forget about <a href="/blog/ws/2016/04/19/customer-marketing-strategies">marketing to your customers</a>.</p>
<p>Last year, in my previous role managing a large set of high-paying and strategic customers, I spent several weeks planning the physical gifts I wanted to mail out to people. I also ordered a huge set of family-style holiday postcards with festive pictures of my colleagues on them and organized a card-writing party.</p>
<p>Small acts of personalized kindness towards your customers make a huge impact and can strengthen the relationship, turning a happy customer into a <a href="/blog/ws/2017/02/24/brand-advocacy-paid-social">brand advocate</a>.</p>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-appreciation-email"></div>
<h3>15. Send out a (good!) customer appreciation email</h3>
<p>This is the time of year to reach out to your customers, thank them for their loyalty, and wish them a happy holiday season. Though a short piece of content, there are a lot of dos and don&#8217;ts here. Check out our post on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/11/29/holiday-customer-appreciation-letter">creative holiday greetings and messages to send to your customers</a> to get the tips and templates you need.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/holiday-customer-appreciation-message-example-later.png" alt="holiday customer greeting example" width="550" height="529" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-50206" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/holiday-customer-appreciation-message-example-later.png 550w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/holiday-customer-appreciation-message-example-later-480x462.png 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 550px, 100vw" /></p>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-year-in-review-email"></div>
<h3>16. Try a year-in-review email</h3>
<p>This email is different from a holiday greeting. Instead, it gives a more specific wrap-up from the year and can take a few different forms. When done right, it can engage your readers, attract new customers, and encourage existing ones to stay on board with you in the coming year. Check out these <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/12/08/year-in-review-email-examples">unforgettable year-in-review email examples and tips</a> for inspiration.</p>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-playlist"></div>
<h3>17. Create a shareable holiday playlist</h3>
<p>The holidays are an unquestionably upbeat time of year. Many of your customers are likely taking time off to relax and listen to the sweet sounds of the season. Connect with them through music by creating a shareable holiday playlist on a public streaming platform, like<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/07/13/spotify-advertising" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Spotify</a> or Pandora.</p>
<p>A <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/video-marketing-for-small-business/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">holiday marketing idea</a> like this can provide you with engaging content for social media, where you might promote your playlist by sharing individual songs or spreading the word in your posts or stories. Ask your followers to comment with their favorite holiday tunes. You could even create an Instagram Story poll that asks your audience what songs they might want to have added. As a bonus, you could play the playlist in your store or office all winter! Just be sure to include your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/11/08/business-name-ideas" target="_blank" rel="noopener">business name</a> or logo in the playlist name or on your streaming profile. That way, you‚Äôll stay top-of-mind to your customers as they listen along with you.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/holiday-marketing-ideas-playlist.jpg" alt="holiday marketing ideas - shareable playlist" width="900" height="356" class="aligncenter wp-image-87537 size-full" srcset="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/holiday-marketing-ideas-playlist.jpg 900w, https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/holiday-marketing-ideas-playlist-480x190.jpg 480w" sizes="(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 900px, 100vw" /></p>
<div id="holiday-marketing-ideas-ai"></div>
<h3>18. Use AI to create unique holiday marketing copy and creative assets</h3>
<p>There are tons of ways you can leverage <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2023/11/20/ai-holiday-marketing" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AI in your holiday marketing¬†</a>to help you quickly create holiday campaigns that pop at scale. For example, you could use an<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-copywriting-tools" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> AI copywriting tool</a> to rewrite your go-to ad or email copy to be holiday-themed. There are also a ton of AI-powered creative tools, some even directly in Meta Ads and<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/google-ads-holiday-strategies" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Google Ads</a>, to create and edit holiday image and video assets. Just be sure to use a high-quality <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ai-prompts" target="_blank" rel="noopener">AI prompt</a> and give any AI-created assets a final, manual edit before you go live with them to ensure you <a href="https://localiq.com/blog/brand-consistency/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">maintain brand consistency</a> throughout the season.</p>
<h2>Turn your holiday marketing hopes into reality</h2>
<p>Use these¬†<a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2019/08/08/holiday-marketing-tips">holiday marketing tips</a> to make all of your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2021/11/05/december-marketing-ideas">holiday marketing</a> dreams come true! Variety is the theme for this holiday marketing ideas list, as there are countless ways to approach your holiday campaigns. So, be open to trying a few different tactics to cover your bases. Plus, you don&#8217;t have to deal with your holiday marketing alone, either. See how <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/marketing-services?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Demo_Blog_Demo" target="_blank" rel="noopener">our solutions</a> can help you maximize your holiday campaigns for ROI that lasts well after the season is over.</p>
